# Netlify SPA fallback: serve index.html for any path so the React app loads.
# The app uses a HashRouter (routes live after "/#", e.g. /#/interview/142), so
# the server normally only ever sees "/". This catch-all still matters so a
# hashless URL (a typed address or an old shared link) does not 404 at Netlify's
# edge before React loads; the app then resolves it client-side. NOTE: shareable
# links MUST be hash-rooted (/#/...) to reopen the right view; see buildShareUrl
# in src/utils/share.js.
#
# /retrieve and /.netlify/functions/* are still handled by the Function runtime
# (Netlify routes function paths before this catch-all).
/*    /index.html   200
